article.headline: Southern 69, Miss. Valley St. 65
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- Peter Cipriano recorded a double-double of 12 points and 10 rebounds to help lead Southern University to a 69-65 Southwestern Athletic Conference win over Mississippi Valley State Monday night. Jerimie Collier led the Jaguars (8-7, 5-1 SWAC) with 15 points. Alvin Mott added 11 and Chris Alexander had 10. Trayvean Scott dished out six assists. MVSU (5-9, 3-2) got 18 points and seven assists from Hosea Butler. Jesse Taylor added 15 points. The Delta Devils led 28-24 at the half, but the Jaguars outscored them 45-37 in the second. Southern also scored 23 points off MVSU turnovers, while MVSU scored 14 off Jaguar turnovers.
